                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. is worn and shows traces of intensive
                           use. &#xD; &#xD; The back board is damaged by insects.&#xD; The original
                           binding is for the most part destroyed. &#xD; The original sewing is only
                           occasionally visible (e.g., <locus target="#10r">10r</locus>, 19r, 26r,
                           36r, 39r, 47r).&#xD; The sewing has been crudely repaired with three
                           different types of recent threads (e.g., close to the head: <locus from="26r" to="50r">26r-50r</locus>; close to the tail: 9r-25r,
                           40r-50r). &#xD; The leaves of the quires are held together with parchment
                           strips. &#xD; Some fols. are affected by humidity (e.g., <locus from="15r" to="20r">15r-20r</locus>).&#xD; &#xD; f. 1 is of irregular
                           shape.&#xD; f. 4 is mutilated, the upper margin is cut off.&#xD; <locus target="#180">180</locus> is mutilated, 2/3 is cut off.</condition>
